01:04:19,507 --> 01:04:21,161
No.

1361
01:04:21,205 --> 01:04:22,075
No?

1362
01:04:22,119 --> 01:04:23,337
No.

1363
01:04:23,381 --> 01:04:25,774
Statistically you
should be Chinese.

1364
01:04:25,818 --> 01:04:27,341
Huh?

1365
01:04:27,385 --> 01:04:31,171
Look, over 60% of the
people in the world are Asian.

1366
01:04:31,215 --> 01:04:34,609
Therefore, statistically
most people are Asian.

1367
01:04:34,653 --> 01:04:38,265
You are a person, so--

1368
01:04:38,309 --> 01:04:40,354
they're just numbers, James.

1369
01:04:40,398 --> 01:04:42,661
When you get ready
to take a penalty,

1370
01:04:42,704 --> 01:04:45,620
no number tells what you
are thinking or feeling.

1371
01:04:45,664 --> 01:04:48,841
Statistics only know
what happened last time.

1372
01:04:48,885 --> 01:04:50,974
This time, that's up to you.

1373
01:04:51,017 --> 01:04:52,149
Thanks, coach.

1374
01:04:52,192 --> 01:04:53,672
Don't thank me.

1375
01:04:53,715 --> 01:04:54,978
Start playing with
your team again.

1376
01:05:01,985 --> 01:05:05,336
TOMMY: We are here to mark
this momentous occasion.

1377
01:05:05,379 --> 01:05:09,427
Samuel Banks, do you wish to
join in this noble assembly?

1378
01:05:09,470 --> 01:05:10,645
Uh, huh.

1379
01:05:10,689 --> 01:05:12,038
I mean, yes.

1380
01:05:12,082 --> 01:05:14,954
And are you qualified
to serve in our ranks?

1381
01:05:14,998 --> 01:05:17,087
Yes my dad moved
out last night.

1382
01:05:17,130 --> 01:05:20,873
Then I dub thee a fully
qualified member of the Loyal

1383
01:05:20,917 --> 01:05:24,398
Order of Divorce, ready
to join us in our fight

1384
01:05:24,442 --> 01:05:26,270
against the non-divorced.

1385
01:05:26,313 --> 01:05:29,664
[music playing]

1386
01:06:03,742 --> 01:06:06,614
[water bubbling]

1387
01:06:30,812 --> 01:06:32,031
Owe.

1388
01:06:32,075 --> 01:06:33,641
Sorry.

1389
01:06:33,685 --> 01:06:36,253
Why didn't you just
ring the doorbell?

1390
01:06:36,296 --> 01:06:37,732
Uh-- I don't know.

1391
01:06:44,478 --> 01:06:46,132
Look I'm sorry.

1392
01:06:46,176 --> 01:06:48,569
I didn't really
mean to break up.

1393
01:06:48,613 --> 01:06:50,658
Then how come you did?

1394
01:06:50,702 --> 01:06:52,878
Well, I guess because I
listened to something really

1395
01:06:52,921 --> 01:06:54,749
dumb someone told me.

1396
01:06:54,793 --> 01:06:56,969
This whole war thing is dumb.

1397
01:06:57,013 --> 01:06:58,144
Well, I liked the
club when it was

1398
01:06:58,188 --> 01:07:00,886
just us talking about stuff.

1399
01:07:00,929 --> 01:07:02,279
I mean, now it's kind of weird.

1400
01:07:04,977 --> 01:07:06,979
So you don't mean to join?

1401
01:07:07,023 --> 01:07:08,589
I don't want you to
make your parents breakup.

1402
01:07:08,633 --> 01:07:09,503
It's not fun.

1403
01:07:09,547 --> 01:07:10,722
I know.

1404
01:07:10,765 --> 01:07:12,376
[sneezing]

1405
01:07:13,420 --> 01:07:16,206
Oh, no.

1406
01:07:16,249 --> 01:07:18,077
Hey, are we having
a meeting tonight?

1407
01:07:18,121 --> 01:07:20,645
No, everyone is getting
ready for the test.

1408
01:07:20,688 --> 01:07:22,429
Tommy says we should
put the war on hold

1409
01:07:22,473 --> 01:07:23,952
till after the test.

1410
01:07:23,996 --> 01:07:24,866
Then we'll knock them out.

1411
01:07:33,614 --> 01:07:35,051
Hey, Sam.

1412
01:07:35,094 --> 01:07:37,531
We'll have a meeting
next week or something.

1413
01:07:37,575 --> 01:07:39,098
It's OK.

1414
01:07:39,142 --> 01:07:40,621
I don't care about
that war stuff so much.

1415
01:07:40,665 --> 01:07:42,754
I just wanted to hang
out or something.

1416
01:07:42,797 --> 01:07:43,711
You OK.

1417
01:07:43,755 --> 01:07:44,582
Yeah, just--

1418
01:07:44,625 --> 01:07:46,105
What?

1419
01:07:46,149 --> 01:07:48,151
Like Sunday, the car
races were on, Formula One.

1420
01:07:48,194 --> 01:07:49,717
Yeah.

1421
01:07:49,761 --> 01:07:51,589
