1628
01:20:54,545 --> 01:20:55,328
Hi.

1629
01:21:00,725 --> 01:21:01,900
Tony, here he comes.

1630
01:21:01,944 --> 01:21:03,597
Throw it.

1631
01:21:03,641 --> 01:21:06,687
Oop, almost.

1632
01:21:06,731 --> 01:21:10,169
Hey, Mr. Roberts, go long.

1633
01:21:10,213 --> 01:21:13,607
[music playing]

1634
01:21:13,651 --> 01:21:14,478
Got it.

1635
01:21:17,524 --> 01:21:19,439
You OK, Mr. Roberts?

1636
01:21:19,483 --> 01:21:20,397
Oh, yeah.

1637
01:21:20,440 --> 01:21:21,441
Oh, yeah.

1638
01:21:21,485 --> 01:21:23,922
We got all the test for you.

1639
01:21:23,966 --> 01:21:25,924
Thank you.

1640
01:21:25,968 --> 01:21:28,448
All right, let's try that again.

1641
01:21:28,492 --> 01:21:29,362
Here's your pen.

1642
01:21:29,406 --> 01:21:30,189
See you tomorrow.

1643
01:21:32,757 --> 01:21:33,540
Yes.

1644
01:21:42,593 --> 01:21:43,507
[knocking]

1645
01:21:43,550 --> 01:21:44,508
Hi.

1646
01:21:44,551 --> 01:21:45,335
Hi.

1647
01:21:50,514 --> 01:21:52,733
Well, I have
something to tell you.

1648
01:21:52,777 --> 01:21:55,301
I'm going to have to go
away for a little while.

1649
01:21:55,345 --> 01:21:56,607
I know.

1650
01:21:56,650 --> 01:21:57,695
You do.

1651
01:21:57,738 --> 01:21:59,392
I saw you get your showcase.

1652
01:21:59,436 --> 01:22:01,090
Yeah, well, I
have to go to Denver

1653
01:22:01,133 --> 01:22:02,700
for this teaching
conference, and I think

1654
01:22:02,743 --> 01:22:03,962
I'm going to be gone from--
- What?

1655
01:22:04,006 --> 01:22:04,963
Thursday to--

1656
01:22:05,007 --> 01:22:06,573
But I thought you were--

1657
01:22:06,617 --> 01:22:07,879
What?

1658
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:09,881
I thought you were
getting divorced.

1659
01:22:09,925 --> 01:22:11,622
Divorced?

1660
01:22:11,665 --> 01:22:15,365
Well, you and dad
were arguing so much.

1661
01:22:15,408 --> 01:22:17,584
Oh, honey, well,
sure we argue.

1662
01:22:17,628 --> 01:22:19,456
I mean people do sometimes.

1663
01:22:19,499 --> 01:22:23,112
But your dad and I love
each other an awful lot.

1664
01:22:23,155 --> 01:22:24,678
I'm sorry you thought that.

1665
01:22:33,165 --> 01:22:34,384
KAREN: Guess what?

1666
01:22:34,427 --> 01:22:35,733
My parents aren't
getting divorced.

1667
01:22:35,776 --> 01:22:37,778
My mom just had a
conference in Denver.

1668
01:22:37,822 --> 01:22:38,954
They're not?

1669
01:22:38,997 --> 01:22:40,390
No, so they were just arguing.

1670
01:22:40,433 --> 01:22:41,521
So we were totally clueless.

1671
01:22:41,565 --> 01:22:42,435
That's great.

1672
01:22:42,479 --> 01:22:43,741
What's great?

1673
01:22:43,784 --> 01:22:45,308
Karen's aren't
getting a divorce.

1674
01:22:45,351 --> 01:22:46,570
That's their choice.

1675
01:22:46,613 --> 01:22:47,701
And that's not all.

1676
01:22:47,745 --> 01:22:49,225
You know that test?

1677
01:22:49,268 --> 01:22:51,662
I got one from my dad
and I filled it all out

1678
01:22:51,705 --> 01:22:53,229
and put it in the file for you.

1679
01:22:53,272 --> 01:22:54,360
You what?
Oh, no.

1680
01:22:54,404 --> 01:22:55,274
What?

1681
01:22:55,318 --> 01:22:56,667
I did the same thing.

1682
01:22:56,710 --> 01:22:58,625
Now there are two test
with your name on it.

1683
01:22:58,669 --> 01:23:00,236
Great.

1684
01:23:00,279 --> 01:23:02,412
So now just not only flunk,
I get busted for cheating.

1685
01:23:02,455 --> 01:23:04,022
OK, let's not panic here.

1686
01:23:04,066 --> 01:23:05,763
All we have to do is--

1687
01:23:05,806 --> 01:23:09,593
uh-- sneak into the classroom
and take away the extra tests.

1688
01:23:09,636 --> 01:23:11,029
Yeah, right.

1689
01:23:11,073 --> 01:23:12,683
Yeah, my dad's not
finished grading them yet.

1690
01:23:12,726 --> 01:23:14,293
OK, we've only got
a couple of minutes.

1691
01:23:14,337 --> 01:23:15,207
So let's--

1692
01:23:15,251 --> 01:23:16,817
No, no.

1693
01:23:16,861 --> 01:23:18,210
Don't help me any more.

1694
01:23:18,254 --> 01:23:19,777
Thank you very much.

1695
01:23:19,820 --> 01:23:21,605
I'll do this one myself.

1696
01:23:21,648 --> 01:23:25,000
[music playing]

1697
01:23:43,453 --> 01:23:44,715
James, can I help
you find something?

1698
01:23:58,250 --> 01:24:03,516
James, Mr. Roberts would
like to speak with you.

1699
01:24:03,560 --> 01:24:05,388
Come on in, James.

1700
01:24:15,354 --> 01:24:18,444
You know our attitude
towards cheating.

1701
01:24:18,488 --> 01:24:20,620
It cuts against everything
we try to do here.

1702
01:24:20,664 --> 01:24:25,190
It's one of the most serious
offenses a student can commit.

1703
01:24:25,234 --> 01:24:28,106
Now this is what's
going to happen.

1704
01:24:28,150 --> 01:24:31,066
The two false tests
will be thrown out.

1705
01:24:31,109 --> 01:24:34,112
And I'll be having a little
talk with Tommy and my daughter.

1706
01:24:34,156 --> 01:24:36,984
See teachers, even
the slower ones,

1707
01:24:37,028 --> 01:24:39,596
get to recognize their
students handwriting.

1708
01:24:39,639 --> 01:24:41,119
It wasn't really their fault.

1709
01:24:41,163 --> 01:24:42,207
And now to you.

1710
01:24:45,297 --> 01:24:49,519
You will stay after school
today and take a makeup test.

1711
01:24:49,562 --> 01:24:52,087
And you can count on the
questions being different.

1712
01:24:52,130 --> 01:24:53,914
That's-- that's all?

1713
01:24:53,958 --> 01:24:55,916
Would you prefer
electrocution?

1714
01:24:55,960 --> 01:24:57,483
Well, no, sir.

1715
01:24:57,527 --> 01:24:59,746
But why?

1716
01:24:59,790 --> 01:25:01,400
Well, because one
of your classmates

1717
01:25:01,444 --> 01:25:03,881
broke the sacred
kid vow of silence

1718
01:25:03,924 --> 01:25:05,622
and told me what happened
on the day of the test

1719
01:25:05,665 --> 01:25:07,102
and what you did for Sam.

1720
01:25:07,145 --> 01:25:08,929
Oh.

1721
01:25:08,973 --> 01:25:10,148
OK.

1722
01:25:10,192 --> 01:25:11,671
That's it.

1723
01:25:11,715 --> 01:25:14,457
Just be ready for that
test at the end of the day.

1724
01:25:14,500 --> 01:25:17,764
Thank you, Mr. Roberts.

1725
01:25:17,808 --> 01:25:19,592
Who told you?

1726
01:25:19,636 --> 01:25:23,161
Sorry, there's a teacher
vow of silence too.

1727
01:25:23,205 --> 01:25:26,077
[music playing]

1728
01:26:00,067 --> 01:26:02,200
Hey, wake up, sleepy head.

1729
01:26:02,244 --> 01:26:05,029
Come on, you don't want to
be late for your first day

1730
01:26:05,072 --> 01:26:06,204
at the big school.

1731
01:26:06,248 --> 01:26:07,205
No way.

1732
01:26:07,249 --> 01:26:08,119
Come on.

1733
01:26:17,172 --> 01:26:19,086
Getting big.

1734
01:26:19,130 --> 01:26:22,002
[music playing]

1735
01:26:46,418 --> 01:26:47,332
Yes I understand that.

1736
01:26:47,376 --> 01:26:50,161
But I have a schedule too.

1737
01:26:50,205 --> 01:26:51,989
Look, let's just talk
about it later, OK?

1738
01:26:54,731 --> 01:26:58,300
Your father is driving me crazy.

1739
01:26:58,343 --> 01:27:00,302
He's got a meeting
on Friday and he

1740
01:27:00,345 --> 01:27:01,955
can't pick you up until 6:00.

1741
01:27:01,999 --> 01:27:06,743
But he knows very well that
I have a class that night.

1742
01:27:06,786 --> 01:27:09,224
Ah, well, I got an idea.

1743
01:27:09,267 --> 01:27:14,011
I could go to school with you,
hang out at the snack bar,

1744
01:27:14,054 --> 01:27:15,839
and he could pick me up there.

1745
01:27:15,882 --> 01:27:17,362
That would work.
That would work.

1746
01:27:17,406 --> 01:27:18,189
That's great.

1747
01:27:21,061 --> 01:27:22,454
Thank you.

1748
01:27:22,498 --> 01:27:24,761
Oh, you are so my son right now.

1749
01:27:33,987 --> 01:27:35,946
I'm telling you, divorce
can be the greatest thing

1750
01:27:35,989 --> 01:27:37,077
that ever happened to you.

1751
01:27:37,121 --> 01:27:37,991
Hey, Tommy.

1752
01:27:38,035 --> 01:27:39,254
Oh, hey, James.

1753
01:27:39,297 --> 01:27:42,344
It's all here in my newsletter.

1754
01:27:42,387 --> 01:27:43,606
Guys ready for the big time?

1755
01:27:43,649 --> 01:27:44,520
Yeah.

1756
01:27:44,563 --> 01:27:47,131
No more baby school.

1757
01:27:47,174 --> 01:27:49,046
Whoops, sorry, Karen.

1758
01:27:49,089 --> 01:27:50,090
It's OK, Ernie.

1759
01:27:50,134 --> 01:27:51,744
I'll see you guys next year.

1760
01:27:51,788 --> 01:27:53,093
And I'll see you after school.

1761
01:27:53,137 --> 01:27:53,877
Sure.

1762
01:27:56,706 --> 01:27:59,143
Kind of neat to be
taking a bus, huh?

1763
01:27:59,186 --> 01:28:01,406
Nah, I kind of
miss the old bridge.

1764
01:28:01,450 --> 01:28:02,277
Me too.

1765
01:28:08,674 --> 01:28:13,418
Billy, I saved
you a jelly donut.

1766
01:28:13,462 --> 01:28:14,245
No way.

1767
01:28:17,074 --> 01:28:19,337
I'm sick of sex.

1768
01:28:28,172 --> 01:28:31,697
[music playing]

